  "codexEntries": [
    {
      "id": "34dc0e97-09b9-483b-9a15-6b787687d977",
      "category": "bestiary",
      "entityId": "Giant_Weasel",
      "title": "The Colossal Weasel: A Predator of Legend",
      "content": "The Giant Weasel, a creature of immense size and cunning, is a formidable predator that stalks the wilds of the realm. Standing as tall as a man and stretching over twice as long, this monstrous weasel is a sight to behold, with a sleek, muscular body covered in glossy, dark fur that seems to absorb the light. Its eyes, a piercing yellow, hold an intelligence that is both chilling and awe-inspiring.\n\n**Biology**: The Giant Weasel is believed to be a distant cousin of the common weasel, magnified to monstrous proportions by the wild magic that permeates the realm. Its biology is a marvel of nature, with a heart that beats slowly but powerfully, pumping blood through a body designed for speed and agility. Its teeth, sharp as daggers, are said to be enchanted, capable of piercing even the toughest armor.\n\n**Ecology**: These giants are solitary creatures, marking vast territories that they defend with ferocious tenacity. They are known to burrow extensive networks of tunnels, using them to ambush prey or escape danger. Their diet consists mainly of large game, but they are not above scavenging or attacking unwary adventurers. Despite their fearsome reputation, Giant Weasels are elusive, and sightings are rare.\n\n**Myths and Lore**: Many tales speak of the Giant Weasel's intelligence and cunning. Some say they can understand and mimic human speech, using it to lure unwary travelers into traps. Others tell of weasels that have formed pacts with dark sorcerers, serving as their familiar and enforcer. The most chilling myth is that of the Weasel King, a Giant Weasel said to rule over a kingdom of smaller weasels, waiting for the day it will rise to claim the realm for its own.\n\n**Adventurer's Tale**: 'I thought I was prepared for anything, but nothing could have ready me for the sight of that beast. It was like a shadow given form, all muscle and teeth and eyes that burned like lanterns in the dark. I fought it, but it was like fighting a storm. In the end, it was my wits, not my sword, that saved me. I'll never forget the look in its eyes, though. It was like it was laughing at me, like it knew it could have ended me at any moment. I escaped with my life, but I'll never forget the Giant Weasel.' - Thalion Swiftshadow, Ranger of the Silverwood.",
      "isNew": false,
      "discoveredAt": 6700
    }
  ],
